{*}When we came back from holiday,Tom, our neighbour,told us this story:
"We were in bed when I heard a chopping noise coming from your lounge.I didn't think much about it and tried to get to sleep.The chopping noise didn't stop,so I went downstairs and then round to your house to see what was going on.I looked into your lounge and saw {an axe}lying on the floor.It frightened me a little,at first,but then I thought you must have left it there by accident."
{* We hadn't. { After Tom told us this I was frightened,although I don't think about it any more. {* We still don't know how the axe got {into the lounge.}
